08/03/2011
VIENNA, Austria -- President Heinz Fischer said on Monday (March 7th) that his country would back Bulgaria's Schengen accession without any additional conditions and help prepare for it. 
Fischer was speaking at a joint press conference with Bulgarian counterpart Georgi Parvanov after a meeting in Vienna. 
Parvanov reiterated Bulgaria's determination to meet all technical criteria to become part of the border free-zone by mid-March. 
"We hope that Bulgaria will become a Schengen member in the frames of the Hungarian EU Presidency," he said. 
(Focus, Standart, 24 Chasa - 07/03/11)
